cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the recognition of a specific class of intersection graphs (EPG graphs) and their variants (Helly-$B_k$ EPG graphs) which are related to topics in discrete mathematics (combinatorics and graph theory) and computational geometry (grid representations). Therefore, cs.DM and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of the complexity of the recognition problem, which is a fundamental question in theoretical computer science, and thus cs.DS and cs.CC are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses some results from the theory of graphs and hypergraphs, which suggests that cs.GT is a possible sub-category as well.
